<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Typeform: Test OAuth Scopes</title>
    <style>
        body {
            --accent: #d8495a;
            --soft: #e8e8e8;

            font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            color: #262627;
            background-color: #fafafa;
        }

        nav {
            background-color: #ffffff;
            color: #4c4c4c;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ededed;
            padding: 20px 10px;
        }

        nav ul {
            max-width: 960px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0;
        }

        nav li {
            list-style-type: none;
            display: inline-block;
        }

        nav a {
            font-size: 18px;
            background: #F0F0F0;
            text-decoration: none;
            padding: 10px;
            display: block;
            color: #4c4c4c;
        }

        nav a:visited {
            color: inherit;
        }

        nav a:hover {
            background-color: #f5f5f5;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        main,
        header {
            max-width: 960px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 0 30px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .btn {
            color: #fff;
            font-size: 15px;
            background: var(--accent);
            display: inline-block;
            border: none;
            padding: 3px 12px;
            min-width: 120px;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .btn:hover {
            cursor: pointer;
            background-color: #ef6474;
        }

        span {
            font-family: monospace;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 105%;
            background-color: var(--soft);
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <nav>
        <ul>
            <% if (user) { %>
                <li>
                    <a href="/auth/logout">Log out</a>
                </li>
                <%} else { %>
                    <li>
                        <a href="/auth/login">Login</a>
                    </li>
                    <% } %>

                        <li>
                            <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a>
                        </li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    <header>
        <h1>Disclaimer:</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <p>All of the
            <b>POST</b> buttons *will* create things in the account you used to sign in.You have been warned! So you will need
            forms:write and webhooks:write scopes too, but theyâ€™re set up automatically when you select it.
        </p>
        <p>
            <b>Read Webhooks</b> actually sets up a form and a webhook for it before it fetches it. So you will need
            <span>forms:write</span> and
            <span>webhooks:write</span> scopes too.
        </p>
        <p>
            <b>Write Webhooks</b> actually sets up a webhook for one of your forms before it fetches it. So you will need
            <span>forms:read</span> scope too.</p>
        <p>But worry not, these dependencies are handled by the scopes selection screen ;)</p>

    </main>
</body>

</html>